'''Erica Rose Campbell''' (born May 12, 1981, in [[Deerfield, New Hampshire]])<ref name="playboybio">{{cite web|title= Erica Campbell biography at Playboy.com|publisher=Playboy|url= http://www.playboy.com/girls/cybergirls/week/20060601/|accessdate = 2007-09-11}}</ref> is a former [[United States|American]] [[glamour model]].

==Career==
Campbell was the [[Playboy Special Edition]]s Model of the Year for 2005<ref name="ec">{{cite web|title= Erica Campbell|publisher= [[Playboy]]|url= http://www.playboy.com/specialeditions/directory/models/campbell-erica.html|accessdate= 2008-08-21}}</ref>. She was also the Mystique Magazine Model Safari winner in 2003, and has been featured on modeling Web sites including her own, www.ericacampbell.com <ref name=xfanz>{{cite web | author = Tod Hunter | title = Tough Call | url = http://www.xfanz.com/news/93758 | date = 2008-05-12 | accessdate = 2008-05-12 | publisher = XFanz}}</ref>

Campbell was named Playboy.com's Cyber Girl of the Week for the first week of June 2006,<ref name="cgw">{{cite web|title= Cybergirl of the Week 2006 Directory|publisher= Playboy|url= http://www.playboy.com/girls/cybergirls/week/2006.html|accessdate= 2007-09-11}}</ref> Cyber Girl of the Month for October 2006, and [[Penthouse (magazine)|Penthouse]] Pet of the Month for April 2007.<ref name="ph">{{cite web|title= Erica Campbell <U+2013> Penthouse Pet of the Month <U+2013> April 2007|publisher= Penthouse|url = http://www.penthouse.com|accessdate= 2007-03-24}}</ref>

==Personal life==
On May 11, 2008 she announced via a letter posted on her Web site that she had retired from adult entertainment and is now a Christian.<ref name=xfanz />

